Package com.orbitz.monitoring.lib.processor

Interface Summary
MonitorSampler Samples from a population of monitors
 

Class Summary
AggregationMonitorProcessor MonitorProcessor that delegates to an Aggregator.
AsyncMonitorProcessor Processes monitors on a separate thread.
ConcurrencyMonitorProcessor This is an implementation of the MonitorProcessor interface that maintains counts of concurrently executing transactions.
CPUProfilingMonitorProcessor This is an implementation of the MonitorProcessor interface that uses a ThreadMXBean to determine CPU time used by the current thread within the scope of a TransactionMonitor.
EventPatternLoggingMonitorProcessor A monitor processor that logs the monitors collected to a log4j logger in an event pattern format.
LatencyMonitoringCoverageMonitorProcessor This is an implementation of the MonitorProcessor interface that checks to see if latency > a given threshold and no child monitors are contained within a given TransactionMonitor.
LocationAnnotatingMonitorProcessor LocationAnnotatingMonitorProcessor adds an attribute named "stackTraceElement" to the given Monitor.
LoggingMonitorProcessor This is an implementation of the MonitorProcessor interface that logs Monitor callback events to Log4j.
MonitorProcessorAdapter An abstract adapter class for MonitorProcessors.
PercentageMonitorSampler MonitorSampler that accepts a defined percentage of all monitors
ResultCodeAnnotatingMonitorProcessor ResultCodeAnnotatingMonitorProcessor will set the resultCode attribute with the failureThrowable class's name.
ThreadContentionMonitorProcessor This is an implementation of the MonitorProcessor interface that reports synchronization statistics for the current thread within the scope of a TransactionMonitor.
XmlLoggingMonitorProcessor A monitor processor that logs the monitors collected to a log4j logger in an XML format.
